parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, leak oil, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes loud clanking noises
loses power
leaks oil
and may cause the wheels to lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, grind gears, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission grinds gears
makes loud noises
and may cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the output shaft can cause the vehicle to lose power, seize, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The output shaft breaks
strips
or twists
causing the vehicle to lose power or seize.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the driver or passenger in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract properly
leaving excessive slack
the seat belt gets stuck in the door
the seat belt does not lock when braking
the seat belt does not tighten when buckled
the seat belt must be manually pulled back into the retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Missing or Loose Front Control Arm Bolt
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A missing or loose front control arm bolt can cause the front suspension to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The left front suspension comes apart
the wheel jams up under the car or fender
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the front end of the vehicle collapses.
